snippet.textDisplay:
When you later knows, he's being forced to fight against his wish by the goverment. He's doing this just to free his wife and daughter.

Those lightning veins of his body is due to a lightning strike he took at age of 12. He was miraculously saved and in effect he grew very tall. He was hailed as a national hero in Muay Thai at the age of 18. He got married shortly after and they got a child.

At the age of 24, he met an unknown military group (match-fixer) who wanted to give Fahkumram a massive sum in order him to lose a fight, or should he fail, they will subsequently threaten him with physical harm. (similar how Steve Fox had in Tekken 4). Since 'Ram is having none of that, he knocked out the challenger in a single hit after the gong started. The match-fixing gang got furious and tried to murder him, but they were no match against 'Ram, as he managed to kill several of them in defense.

The cops shortly arrived after the scene, arresting him, (both policemen and soldiers were corrupted by the same military group that Ram met earlier. They even held his wife and daughter as hostage, which giving Ram no choice but to follow their orders.

He's been forced to participate in secret underground martial arts competition and show-fights, fighting tigers and other wild animals (hence the scar on his face). This made him more desperate and disillusioned, by the fact he is unable to see a way out of this, as he gradually lose himself in this extreme act of violence and rage.

4 years later, The fight between Mishima Zaibatsu and G-Corporation is stirring, and the military sees the Zaibatsu as their threat to the nation. So they dispatch Fahkumram for the mission, to participate The King of Iron Fist Tournament and claim the victory there. They promise Ram to set his family free if he fulfills his role they will achieve. Fahkumram joins the fray, determined to win the tournament in order to set his family free.


So yeah, the thing he says "how many left?" is he thinking when will this end so he can go back to his family life. He was represented as a national hero in the past by his genius talent in Muay Thai, only to be used against his will by the corrupted military for illegal betting.

Not only he was fighting for his family, but he himself is innocent.

snippet.textDisplay:
Tekken 7 eSport scene is amazing but how it can be the same for the game.

I'm a huge fan of Tekken but i feel for non tournament player the game is quite empty

- bad online, 3bars, input lag
- lack of content (survive mode, team battle, tekken ball)
- bad character ending
- bad personnalisation
- Some stage are the same
- Dubstep again, where are the music like tekken 4

I feel that this game has no soul like the others like tekken 3 or 4.
